OL,5, Commons Speaker Sir Lindsay Hoyle says 
OL,6, he has been "heavily lobbied" by women 
OL,7, MPs not to change the rules on bringing
OL,8, babies into the chamber.               
OL,10,FEarlier this week Labour's Stella      
OL,11,FCreasy was told it was against         
OL,12,F"behaviour and courtesies" rules to    
OL,13,Fbring her three-month-old into debates.
OL,15,FShe said MPs were not able to take     
OL,16,Fmaternity leave, so the rules needed to
OL,17,Fhelp "parenting and politics to mix".  
OL,19,FSir Lindsay has asked a committee of   
OL,20,FMPs to review the rules.               
